===Etymology 1===
{{PIE root|en|kʷyeh₁}}
The first word of the [[introit]] for the traditional requiem mass, an alternative [[accusative case]] of {{der|en|la|requiēs||rest, repose}}, from {{m|la|re-||again}} + {{m|la|quiēs||rest, quiet}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[mass]] (especially Catholic) to [[honor]] and remember a dead person.
# A [[musical]] [[composition]] for such a mass.
